author: Ed Guzman
title: Watch: Seahawks retake lead over Panthers as Marshawn Lynch ties for second-most rushing TDs in Seattle history
text:
Watch: Seahawks retake lead over Panthers as Marshawn Lynch ties for second-most rushing TDs in Seattle history Originally published October 18, 2015 at 2:11 pm Updated October 18, 2015 at 2:21 pm Seahawks running back Marshawn Lynch punches through for a touchdown in the second quarter against the Carolina Panthers on Sunday at CenturyLink Field. (Dean Rutz / The Seattle Times) The Seahawks pulled ahead once more on Marshawn Lynch's first rushing touchdown of the season. 
One sustained drive deserves another, apparently. 
The Seahawks put together their best drive of the game so far on Sunday, a 12-play drive that went 90 yards in 5:30 and was capped off by a Marshawn Lynch 1-yard touchdown run with 8 minutes to go. It was Lynch’s first touchdown of the season. 
The touchdown was Lynch’s 55th with the Seahawks, tying Curt Warner for the second-most rushing TDs in Seahawks history. Shaun Alexander holds the record with 100. SEAHAWKS vs. PANTHERS »
